misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that computing the numerator (v1 - v0) separately and then dividing by t is equivalent to the mathematical formula a = (v1 - v0) / t. However, they have split the calculation into two steps without recognizing that both operations are necessary components of a single formula.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The student correctly implements the mathematical formula a = (v1 - v0) / t in lines 9-10, so there is no actual misconception about the formula itself. The code is correct and will produce the expected output.
